article.headline: IUPUI 77, UMKC 72
article.story: INDIANAPOLIS (AP) -- Craig Swoope scored a career-high 22 points to lead IUPUI to a 77-72 victory over UMKC on Thursday. David Barlow added 19 points, nine rebounds and seven assists for the Jaguars (8-9, 2-2 Mid-Continent Conference). IUPUI opened with a 10-0 run and took a 14-point lead 3:50 into the game. Swoope scored 13 of his points in the first half as IUPUI shot 16-of-30 (53 percent) from the floor to led 42-29 at halftime. Dane Brumagin led UMKC (7-13, 2-2) with 28 points and six rebounds. Dominique Johnson came off the bench to score 17 points and Brent Stephens added 11 points for the Kangaroos. UMKC tied the game at 68-68 on a 3-pointer from Johnson with 3:18 to play, but was unable to take the lead as the Jaguars hit 7-of-8 free throws in the final 1:41.
